SIMPLE: nonnative
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: nonnative
<hw>nonnative</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>not being or
composed of aborigines; <as>as, the <ex>nonnative</ex> population of
South Africa</as>. Opposite of <ant>native</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of persons born in another area or country than that
lived in; foreign-born; <as>as, our large <ex>nonnative</ex>
population</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> foreign-born.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Originating in a different region and acclimated to
a new environment; -- of plants or animals.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> domesticated, naturalized.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nonnatural</ent>⟦br⟧
